reviewText: The man who would be governor and then president steps onto the national political stage for the first time -- and asserts himself as a leader the nation -- decades later -- would recognize it needed. An historical artifact of contemporary value.

Experts across the political spectrum agree this speech was key in ushering in the modern conservative movement. What fascinated me was how different the speech is from what a modern politician would give. The speech is full of details, substance, ideas, rather than just sound bytes or slogans. It definitely has a higher grade level and content level than current speeches on either side.
